---
// src/pages/en/privacy-policy.astro
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const lang = "en";
---

<Layout
    title="Privacy Policy and Legal Notice - Pickleball Águilas Resort"
    lang={lang}
>
    <Navbar />

    <header
        class="relative bg-azul-oscuro py-20 px-6 flex items-center justify-center text-center"
    >
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/40 z-10"></div>
        <div class="relative z-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h1
                class="font-titulos text-4xl md:text-5xl text-white uppercase tracking-tighter shadow-sm"
            >
                Privacy Policy and Legal Notice
            </h1>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main
        class="py-16 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-gray-700 space-y-12 leading-relaxed"
    >
        <div>
            <h2
                class="text-3xl font-titulos text-azul-oscuro mb-8 uppercase border-b-2 border-amarillo-acento pb-2 inline-block"
            >
                PRIVACY POLICY
            </h2>

            <section class="space-y-6">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Information of the website owner
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Registration in the Mercantile Registry with
                        No.:……………………………….
                    </p>
                    <p>Member of ……………………. with No. …………….</p>
                    <p>Authorized Entity ………………………….</p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Data Protection Controller
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        The owner is responsible for the personal data that are
                        collected by browsing and using this website in
                        accordance with the requirements established by
                        REGULATION (EU) 2016/679 relative to the protection of
                        data of natural persons as well as in accordance with
                        Law 34/2002 of July 11 on Information Society Services
                        and Electronic Commerce (LSSI-CE).
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        By using this website we understand that you have read
                        and understood the information set forth in relation to
                        the processing of your personal data.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Data protection policy
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        The controller applies the principle of active
                        responsibility in the processing of personal data,
                        maintaining a constant update and promoting the
                        continuous improvement of the data protection system in
                        accordance with the enforceable legal requirements,
                        guaranteeing in any case:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            respect for the freedoms and fundamental rights of
                            natural persons
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            that the data are processed in a lawful, fair, and
                            transparent manner
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            that the processed data are accurate, adequate,
                            relevant, and limited in relation to the purposes
                            for which they are collected
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            that the purposes for which they are collected are
                            explicit and legitimate and that they are not
                            processed in a manner incompatible with said
                            purposes
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        The purpose of this document is to inform users about
                        what we do with their personal data, how it is
                        collected, what it is used for, the rights that assist
                        them, as well as all the necessary legal information
                        established by current regulations.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Data collected, purpose, and lawfulness
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        The personal data processed are those provided by users
                        through the forms available on this website and are the
                        minimum required to be able to:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            send you information about our products / services.
                        </li>
                        <li>respond to inquiries.</li>
                        <li>
                            process orders, as well as be able to prepare the
                            corresponding invoices, inform about the status of
                            orders, attend to claims, and any other management
                            derived from the provision of the service carried
                            out through this website.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Said purposes are based on legal principles of
                        processing the data collected by current regulations:
                        for the execution of a contract or the provision of a
                        service to users, for the fulfillment of legal
                        obligations, for legitimate interest, and with the
                        consent of users.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Web forms
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Personal data collected through the contact web form are
                        used to attend to any inquiry that the user makes
                        through it.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Personal data collected in the order form have the
                        purpose of processing the data necessary for the correct
                        management of your orders.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        The processing of data is legitimized by the consent you
                        give us by expressly accepting the processing conditions
                        informed through this privacy policy.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Recipients of the data
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Personal data obtained through the web forms are
                        recorded and stored on electronic media controlled and
                        supervised by the data controller.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Your personal data will not be communicated to third
                        parties, with the exception that said data communication
                        is covered by a legal obligation or when for the correct
                        provision of the service or the execution of the
                        contract it is necessary to communicate your data to
                        third parties to be able to effect the payment (payment
                        gateways), as well as manage product deliveries
                        (carriers), said assignment being covered by the needs
                        of the service. Regarding payment through other payment
                        gateways, we recommend the user read the privacy policy
                        to understand how it handles personal information, for
                        example:
                    </p>

                    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg mt-3 text-sm">
                        <p>
                            <strong
                                >Redsys Servicios de Procesamiento, S.L.
                                (“Redsys”)</strong
                            >, with address in Madrid, Francisco Sancha street,
                            number 12, and with C.I.F. number B-85955367, which
                            fully complies with current legislation on the
                            protection of personal data and with the
                            confidentiality commitments typical of its activity.
                            Redsys has adopted the technical measures necessary
                            to maintain the required security level. You can
                            view their privacy policy at <a
                                href="https://www.redsys.es/legal/20180223_politica_de_privacidad_web_publica_redsys.pdf"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-azul-principal hover:underline break-all"
                                >https://www.redsys.es/legal/20180223_politica_de_privacidad_web_publica_redsys.pdf</a
                            >
                        </p>
                        <p class="mt-3">
                            <strong
                                >PayPal (Europe) S.à.r.l. et Cie, S.C.A.</strong
                            >
                            (R.C.S. Luxembourg B 118 349), whose privacy policy establishes
                            the appropriate security measures for the correct processing
                            of users' personal data. You can view their privacy policy
                            at <a
                                href="https://www.paypal.com/es/webapps/mpp/ua/privacy-full?locale.x=es_ES#1"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-azul-principal hover:underline break-all"
                                >https://www.paypal.com/es/webapps/mpp/ua/privacy-full?locale.x=es_ES#1</a
                            >
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <p class="mt-3">
                        For cases in which the communication of data to third
                        parties is not covered by the legal bases established in
                        the previous section, the communication of data to other
                        recipients will only be carried out if the user has
                        given their express consent.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Strict selection criteria for data processors are
                        maintained, along with a contractual commitment with
                        each of them to comply with and enforce the obligations
                        established in matters of data protection.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        In the event that international data transfers exist,
                        TABURETE HOSTEL, SL will guarantee that the transfer of
                        your personal data is carried out in accordance with
                        applicable privacy laws and, in particular, that the
                        necessary contractual, technical, and organizational
                        measures are applied, such as the standard contractual
                        clauses approved by the European Commission.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        You can obtain more information about the processing of
                        personal data from our organization by requesting it at
                        the email: <a
                            href="mailto:EQUIPAZO@TABURETEHOSTEL.COM"
                            class="text-azul-principal hover:underline font-medium"
                            >EQUIPAZO@TABURETEHOSTEL.COM</a
                        > or by accessing through the following link: <a
                            href="https://www.accesousuario.com/protecciondedatos/rgpd/informacion_consentimientoAPI.php?codEmpresa=75680"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-azul-principal hover:underline break-all"
                            >Information on Data Protection</a
                        >
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Technical and organizational data protection measures
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        The media have the necessary technical and
                        organizational measures that guarantee the
                        confidentiality and preservation of personal data
                        obtained through the web.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Personal data collected from the web are processed using
                        HTML protocol with a valid SSL certificate.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        The personnel involved in data processing operations:
                        access, editing, deletion, etc., are qualified for it,
                        trained, and committed to this data protection policy.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Data preservation
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Personal data obtained through the contact form will be
                        kept for the time necessary to attend to the
                        request/inquiry made.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Personal data obtained through the order form will be
                        kept as long as there is a contractual and/or commercial
                        relationship with you or as long as you do not exercise
                        your right to deletion, cancellation, and/or limitation
                        of the processing of your data.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Once the contractual relationship has expired, we will
                        keep the information duly blocked, without giving it any
                        use, while it may be necessary for the exercise or
                        defense of claims or any type of judicial, legal, or
                        contractual responsibility may arise from its
                        processing, which must be attended to and for which its
                        recovery is necessary.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        In case you have expressly accepted the sending of
                        commercial information, we will keep your contact
                        details until you notify us of your decision to cancel
                        said commercial mailings.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Information on the existence of automated decisions
                        (including profiling)
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Normally we do not adopt automated decisions, but when
                        we do, we will make it clear that this type of decision
                        is being adopted. Nevertheless, TABURETE HOSTEL, SL
                        CIF/NIF B73996001 includes several sections dedicated to
                        the personalization of services in order to show
                        personalized advertising when entering its website and
                        also for sending personalized communications.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        TABURETE HOSTEL, SL CIF/NIF B73996001 recognizes the
                        possibility of profiling to improve its product offering
                        or personalize the sending of commercial offers or give
                        more personalized treatment to the customer.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Objection to data being processed for advertising
                        purposes
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        If you gave your consent for your data to be used for
                        advertising purposes and you do not wish to continue
                        receiving advertising, you can revoke the consent
                        granted at any time by sending an email to the
                        controller's email <a
                            href="mailto:EQUIPAZO@TABURETEHOSTEL.COM"
                            class="text-azul-principal hover:underline font-medium"
                            >EQUIPAZO@TABURETEHOSTEL.COM</a
                        >.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Changes to the Privacy Policy
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        We may modify the information contained in this Privacy
                        and Cookies Policy when we deem it convenient. In the
                        event that we do so, we will notify you by various means
                        through the Platform (for example, through a banner, a
                        pop-up, or a push notification), or even communicate it
                        to your email address when the change in question is
                        significant to your privacy, so that you can review the
                        changes, evaluate them and, where appropriate, object or
                        unsubscribe from any service or functionality. In any
                        case, we suggest you review this Privacy and Cookies
                        Policy from time to time in case there are minor changes
                        or we introduce any interactive improvement.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>

        <div class="pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <h2
                class="text-3xl font-titulos text-azul-oscuro mb-8 uppercase border-b-2 border-amarillo-acento pb-2 inline-block"
            >
                LEGAL NOTICE
            </h2>

            <section class="space-y-6">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Intellectual and industrial property
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        The design of the portal and its source codes, as well
                        as the logos, brands, and other distinctive signs that
                        appear on it belong to TABURETE HOSTEL, SL and are
                        protected by the corresponding intellectual and
                        industrial property rights.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Responsibility for content
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        TABURETE HOSTEL, SL CIF/NIF B73996001 is not responsible
                        for the legality of other third-party websites from
                        which the portal can be accessed. Nor does it respond
                        for the legality of other third-party websites that
                        might be linked or linked from this portal.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        TABURETE HOSTEL, SL CIF/NIF B73996001 will not be
                        responsible for the use that third parties make of the
                        information published on the portal, nor for the damages
                        suffered or economic losses that, directly or
                        indirectly, produce or may produce economic, material,
                        or data damages caused by the use of said information.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Reproduction of content
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        By virtue of the provisions of the Intellectual Property
                        Law, the reproduction, distribution, and public
                        communication of all or part of the contents of this
                        website, for commercial purposes on any support and by
                        any technical means, without the authorization of
                        TABURETE HOSTEL, SL are expressly prohibited.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Applicable law
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        TABURETE HOSTEL, SL CIF/NIF B73996001 reserves the right
                        to present civil or criminal actions deemed necessary
                        for the improper use of the Website and contents, or for
                        the breach of these conditions.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        The relationship between the user and TABURETE HOSTEL,
                        SL CIF/NIF B73996001 will be governed by the current
                        regulations applicable in the national territory. Should
                        any controversy arise in relation to the interpretation
                        and/or application of these conditions, the parties will
                        submit the conflicts to ordinary jurisdiction,
                        submitting to the corresponding Judges and Courts
                        according to Law.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Likewise, we inform you that you have a free
                        out-of-court dispute resolution procedure accessible to
                        all citizens; this is the online dispute resolution
                        platform of the European Union, accessible through the
                        following link: <a
                            href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr/main/?event=main.home2.show"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-azul-principal hover:underline break-all"
                            >https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr/main/?event=main.home2.show</a
                        >.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Cookies
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        In the event of using “cookie” technology on the web, it
                        has a specific section that informs you about its
                        existence as well as its usage policy. See the section <a
                            href="/en/cookies-policy"
                            class="text-azul-principal hover:underline font-medium"
                            >“cookies policy”</a
                        >.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        Otherwise, browsing cookies are not used.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Personal data of minors
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        This website is not directed at underage users. If you
                        are a minor, please do not attempt to register as a
                        user. If we discover that we have mistakenly obtained
                        personal information from a minor, we will delete said
                        information as soon as possible.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Exercise of data protection rights
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        In accordance with the rights conferred by current
                        regulations on the protection of personal data, the user
                        may exercise the rights of access, rectification,
                        limitation of processing, deletion, portability, and
                        objection to the processing of their data by directing
                        their request to the indicated postal address or to the
                        email <a
                            href="mailto:EQUIPAZO@TABURETEHOSTEL.COM"
                            class="text-azul-principal hover:underline font-medium"
                            >EQUIPAZO@TABURETEHOSTEL.COM</a
                        >.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        To exercise these rights, you must identify yourself by
                        presenting your ID (DNI/Passport).
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                        For any claim, you may contact the same indicated email.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
